    <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">TESCO Bill Check Online — Tribal Electricity Bill 2026</h1>

    <p class="text-neutral-600 text-lg mb-4"><strong>Tribal Electric Supply Company (TESCO)</strong> is the newest of Pakistan's electricity distribution companies — formed in 2004 to take over the electricity network in the former Federally Administered Tribal Areas (FATA). Following the 2018 merger of FATA with Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, TESCO now serves seven merged districts of KP. With roughly <strong>580,000 consumers</strong> spread across some of the most rugged terrain in Pakistan, TESCO's biggest challenge is delivering services to remote valleys — and that includes billing. Online bill checking is therefore especially valuable for TESCO consumers, since printed bills can take weeks to reach villages in Waziristan or Kurram.</p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-l-4 border-primary-600 p-4 rounded-lg mb-8">
      <p class="font-semibold text-primary-800">Quick Answer: Visit <a href="/tesco-bill/" class="underline">pakistanbill.online/tesco-bill/</a>, enter your <strong>14-digit TESCO reference number</strong> (printed on the top-right of any previous bill), and your current month's electricity bill appears instantly. No login, no app, no fees.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What is TESCO and Where Does It Operate?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">TESCO was created when WAPDA's tribal-area operations were corporatized. The company is headquartered in Peshawar (even though Peshawar itself is served by PESCO) and operates under NEPRA's regulatory framework. Its license area covers the <strong>seven merged districts of KP</strong> (formerly FATA):</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Bajaur</strong> — including Khar, Inayat Kalay, Nawagai</li>
      <li><strong>Mohmand</strong> — including Ghalanai, Ekkaghund</li>
      <li><strong>Khyber</strong> — including Landi Kotal, Jamrud, Bara</li>
      <li><strong>Orakzai</strong> — including Kalaya, Ghiljo</li>
      <li><strong>Kurram</strong> — including Parachinar, Sadda, Alizai</li>
      <li><strong>North Waziristan</strong> — including Miranshah, Razmak, Spinwam</li>
      <li><strong>South Waziristan</strong> — including Wana, Ladha, Sararogha</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">If you live in any of these seven districts, TESCO is your electricity supplier — even if your nearest large city (like Peshawar, Bannu, or Dera Ismail Khan) is served by PESCO. The two companies operate entirely separate billing systems, so make sure you check your bill on the TESCO checker, not PESCO.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Step-by-Step: How to Check Your TESCO Bill Online</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">TESCO bills follow the same format as other WAPDA-derived DISCOs. Here's how to check yours:</p>
    <ol class="space-y-4 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-decimal list-inside">
      <li><strong>Locate your 14-digit TESCO reference number.</strong> Open any previous TESCO bill. The reference number is printed in bold on the <strong>top-right</strong> of the bill, just above the barcode, labeled "Ref. No." or "Reference No." — digits only, no letters or dashes.</li>
      <li><strong>Open the TESCO bill checker.</strong> Go to <a href="/tesco-bill/" class="text-primary-600 underline">pakistanbill.online/tesco-bill/</a>. The page loads quickly even on 2G connections common in remote tribal areas.</li>
      <li><strong>Type your reference number carefully.</strong> Enter all 14 digits. Avoid leading zeros getting cut off when copy-pasting — a common mistake.</li>
      <li><strong>Click "Check Bill".</strong> Your current month's bill loads within 2–5 seconds. You'll see the consumer name, address, billing month, units consumed, total amount payable, and due date.</li>
      <li><strong>Download the PDF.</strong> Click "Download PDF" to save a duplicate copy. This PDF is identical to the printed bill and is accepted at all banks and retail shops for payment.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What Information Appears on Your TESCO Bill?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">TESCO bills follow the standard WAPDA format. Key fields to verify:</p>
    <div class="bg-neutral-900 text-green-400 font-mono rounded-xl p-5 mb-6 text-sm overflow-x-auto">
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-xs mb-2">// TESCO Bill — Top Section</p>
      <p>┌─────────────────────────────────────┐</p>
      <p>│  TESCO Electricity Bill                  │</p>
      <p>│  ┌────────────────────────────────┐    │</p>
      <p class="text-yellow-300">│  │ <strong>Ref. No: 01234567890123</strong>    │    │ ← 14-digit</p>
      <p>│  │ Consumer: [Your Name]          │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ District: [Bajaur/Kurram/etc.] │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Reading Date: 12-June-2026     │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Units Consumed: 220 kWh        │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Protected Subsidy: Applied     │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Current Bill: Rs. 5,210        │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ FPA: Rs. 480                   │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Total Payable: Rs. 5,690       │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Due Date: 28-June-2026         │    │</p>
      <p>│  └────────────────────────────────┘    │</p>
      <p>│  [████████ BARCODE ████████]            │</p>
      <p>└─────────────────────────────────────┘</p>
    </div>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">A note for TESCO consumers: many tribal-area households qualify for <strong>NEPRA's Protected Consumer Subsidy</strong> (200 units or less per month). If your bill shows "Protected" or "Subsidy Applied", you're paying about 30–40% less per unit than unprotected consumers. Use less than 200 units every month to maintain this protected status.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">How to Pay Your TESCO Bill</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">TESCO bills can be paid through all standard channels. In tribal areas, mobile wallets are often more reliable than bank branches:</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg">
        <thead class="bg-neutral-100">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Method</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Where</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Fee</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Notes</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-neutral-200">
          <tr><td class="p-3">JazzCash</td><td class="p-3">App → Utility Bills → Electricity → TESCO</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Best for remote areas</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">EasyPaisa</td><td class="p-3">App → Bills → Electricity → TESCO</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Widely accepted</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">Bank mobile apps</td><td class="p-3">HBL, UBL, MCB, Alfalah, Meezan</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Instant confirmation</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">1Bill vouchers</td><td class="p-3">Any retailer / ATM</td><td class="p-3">Rs. 30–50</td><td class="p-3">Same day</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">Bank branch (KP)</td><td class="p-3">HBL, UBL, MCB, NBP in KP cities</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Bring printed bill</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">TESCO office</td><td class="p-3">Peshawar HQ or circle offices</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Cash only</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">NADRA e-Sahulat</td><td class="p-3">Any NADRA center</td><td class="p-3">Rs. 30</td><td class="p-3">Same day</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">Late payments in TESCO areas incur 5% surcharge the first month and 10% additional in subsequent months. After 60 days of non-payment, the connection may be disconnected — reconnection requires paying all arrears plus Rs. 1,000 reconnection fee.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">TESCO Customer Service & Complaints</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">For complaints about billing, meters, or power outages, TESCO operates several contact channels:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Central helpline:</strong> 111-111-117 (toll-free, 24/7)</li>
      <li><strong>Peshawar head office:</strong> 091-9211888</li>
      <li><strong>Bajaur circle:</strong> 0945-920011</li>
      <li><strong>Khyber circle (Landi Kotal):</strong> 0924-920055</li>
      <li><strong>Kurram circle (Parachinar):</strong> 0928-920022</li>
      <li><strong>North Waziristan (Miranshah):</strong> 0939-920033</li>
      <li><strong>South Waziristan (Wana):</strong> 0934-920044</li>
      <li><strong>Online complaint:</strong> tesco.gov.pk → "Complaints" — generates tracking number</li>
      <li><strong>Email:</strong> info@tesco.gov.pk</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">Power-fault response times in TESCO areas are longer than other DISCOs due to terrain and security — typically 4–6 hours in tehsil headquarters and up to 48 hours in remote areas. For billing disputes, allow 14 working days for resolution.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Tips for TESCO Consumers</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-3 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Always keep last month's bill.</strong> Postal delivery in tribal areas is unreliable. Your reference number never changes — once you've stored it in your phone, you can check future bills without needing the printed copy.</li>
      <li><strong>Stay under 200 units</strong> to qualify for the Protected Consumer Subsidy. This halves your effective tariff rate.</li>
      <li><strong>Pay via JazzCash or EasyPaisa</strong> — bank branches in remote areas often have long queues and limited cash handling capacity.</li>
      <li><strong>Take a photo of your meter reading</strong> every month on the date mentioned as "Reading Date" in your bill. This serves as evidence if there's a billing dispute.</li>
      <li><strong>Report transformer faults immediately</strong> — in summer, tribal-area transformers often trip due to overload. The complaint cell responds faster if you report by phone rather than visiting the office.</li>
      <li><strong>Apply for solar net-metering</strong> if you have a 3 kW+ sanctioned load. Tribal areas get excellent sun and net-metering can eliminate your bill in summer months.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-10">
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to check TESCO bill online?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Go to pakistanbill.online/tesco-bill/ and enter your 14-digit TESCO reference number. Your tribal districts electricity bill loads instantly — free, no login, no app required.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Which areas does TESCO cover?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">TESCO covers the former FATA region — now merged with KP — including Bajaur, Mohmand, Khyber, Orakzai, Kurram, North Waziristan, and South Waziristan districts.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to pay TESCO bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Pay TESCO bill through JazzCash (Utility Bills → Electricity → TESCO → 14-digit reference number), EasyPaisa, bank mobile apps, or any bank branch in KP. Also payable at TESCO circle offices.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">What is the TESCO helpline number?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">TESCO helpline is 111-111-117 from any mobile. The Peshawar regional office can be reached at 091-9211888. TESCO also accepts WhatsApp complaints at the official number listed on tesco.gov.pk.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Can I download a duplicate TESCO bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Yes. Visit pakistanbill.online/tesco-bill/, enter your 14-digit reference number, and click 'Download PDF'. The duplicate is accepted at all banks and retailers in KP.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Why are TESCO bills sometimes delayed?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">TESCO serves remote tribal areas where meter reading is challenging due to terrain, security, and weather. Bills in Waziristan and Kurram can be 7–15 days later than Peshawar. Check online — the bill is generated even when the printed version is delayed in transit.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Is TESCO the same as PESCO?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">No. TESCO covers the seven merged tribal districts (former FATA). PESCO covers the rest of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa including Peshawar, Mardan, Charsadda, Abbottabad. They are separate companies with separate reference number databases.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to apply for a new TESCO connection?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Visit your nearest TESCO circle office with CNIC, property documents, and a filled A&AC Form-1 (available at tesco.gov.pk). New domestic connection fee is Rs. 2,500–6,500 depending on load. Connection is typically activated within 30–60 days depending on the location.</div></details>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-bold text-xl text-primary-900 mb-2">Check Your TESCO Bill Now</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-700 mb-4 text-sm">Free, instant, no login required. Enter your 14-digit reference number.</p>
